===Etymology===
From Greek [[στοχαστικος]], from [[στοχαζεσθαι]] ‘aim at a target, guess’, from [[στοχος]] ‘an aim, a guess’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /stə'kæstɪk/
*{{audio|en-us-stochastic.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æstɪk|-æstɪk]]

=== Adjective ===
{{en-ad|stochastic}}

#[[random]], randomly-determined.
#:*'''1970''': In the evening, while she bathed, waiting for him to enter the bathroom as she powdered her body, he crouched over the blueprints spread between the sofas in the lounge, calculating a '''stochastic''' analysis of the Pentagon car park. — JG Ballard, ''The Atrocity Exhibition''

